<h4>Travel</h4>
<p>
    I'm enthusiastic about travelling, although I frequently find myself having little 
    time to travel. Some of my past destinations include:
</p>
<ul>
    <li>Seattle: although I had little time to see the city, I can feel that 
        Seattle is a nice city in almost all respects. It's nice, vibrant but not 
        too much so, and has a great physical surroding - the mountains of Washington.
    </li>
    <li>New York City: I guess this needs little extra explanation.</li>
    <li>Tokyo: another place that needs little extra explanation.</li>
    <li>
        Sapporo, Hokkaido: Sapporo is much like Boston and rather snowy, but it has a 
        much larger night life scene.
    </li>
    <li>
        Shanghai: well, although very similar NYC and Tokyo it is, Shanghai has a 
        more "commonplace" taste to it, e.g., try out the small eateries during breakfast 
        time!
    </li>
    <li>
        Yunnan, China: one of the popular destinations for tourism and one of 
        my favorites. Yunnan is full of the beauty of nature, different ethnic 
        cultures, and exotic food, but if you are unlucky and unwitting you could 
        run into danger, scams or other kinds of trouble!
    </li>
    <li>
        Australia: Australia is distant and somewhat different from all other parts 
        of the world. Life there is very laid-back and animals are a more common scene 
        than in practically everywhere else.
    </li>
    <li>
        Paris, Rome, Amsterdam, and Berlin: I have been there, but it was really many 
        years ago and I remember little of that. I have plans to revisit them though.
    </li>
</ul><br>

