<h4>Music</h4>
<p>
    I'm no expert on music, but I do have some preferences. For classical music, I like 
    Baroque era works, Frederic Chopin's beautiful piano music, and Giacomo Puccini's 
    operas.
</p>
<p>
    I like to listen to much of (especially 1990s) East Asian popular music in general. As for 
    Taiwanese/Chinese pop, I enjoy Faye Wong [王菲], Jay Chou [周杰倫], Stefanie Yanzi Sun [孫燕姿], S.H.E and 
    Penny Tai's [戴佩妮] music. For J-Pop, artists such as Arai Yumi (Matsutoya Yumi) [松任谷由実], SPEED, Amuro 
    Namie [安室奈美恵], Utada Hikaru [宇多田ヒカル], Perfume and Ikimonogakari [いきものがかり] are among my 
    favorites, but I enjoy most of the 1990s J-Pop scene. In general, I do prefer the "classics".
</p><br>

